{
  "texts": [
    "In short, complexity scores the information gain or cost of changing one's mind (in an information theoretic and thermodynamic sense, respectively).",
    "This means Bayesian belief updating is about finding an accurate explanation that is minimally complex (c.f., Occam's principle).",
    "In an enactive setting-apt for explaining decision-making-beliefs about 'which plan to commit to' are based on the free energy expected under a plausible plan.",
    "This implicit planning as inference can be expressed as minimizing expected free energy (Friston et al., 2010):",
    "Risk is the divergence between probabilistic predictions about outcomes, given a plan, relative to prior preferences."
  ]
}